        <h2>Frame</h2>

      <p>A bicycle <b>frame</b> is the main component of a bicycle, onto which wheels and other components are fitted. The modern and most common frame design  consists of two triangles: a main triangle and a paired rear triangle</p>
      <details class="animation"><summary>Top Tube</summary><p><font color ="#4CC7D3"><b>connects the top of the head tube to the top of the seat tube</b></font></p></details>
      <details> <font color ="#4CC7D3"><b>connects the top of the head tube to the top of the seat tube</b></font><summary>Down Tube</summary></details>
      <details> <font color ="#4CC7D3"><b>contains the seatpost of the bike, which connects to the saddle.</b></font><summary>Seat Tube</summary></details>
      <details> <font color ="#4CC7D3"><b>connects the top of the head tube to the top of the seat tube</b></font><summary>Seat Stay</summary></details>
      <details> <font color ="#4CC7D3"><b>run parallel to the chain, connecting the bottom bracket shel</b></font><summary>Chain Stay</summary></details>
      <h2>Saddle Area</h2>
      <p>A bicycle <b>saddle</b>, often called a seat is one of 5 contact pionts on an upright bicyle, the others being the 2 foot pedals and the 2 handles on the 1 handlebar.</p>
      <details class="animation"><summary>Saddle</summary><p><font color ="#4CC7D3"><b>what a bicyclist sits on</b></font></p></details>
      <details> <font color ="#4CC7D3"><b>connects the saddle to the frame</b></font><summary>Seat Post</summary></details>
      
      <h2>Front Set</h2>
      
      <p>The peripheral portion of the bicycle. Area where steering power comes from as well as braking.</p>
      <details class="animation"><summary>Handlebar Grip</summary><p><font color ="#4CC7D3"><b>base where rider grips the bike</b></font></p></details>
      <details> <font color ="#4CC7D3"><b>connects the top of the head tube to the top of the seat tube</b></font><summary>Head Tube</summary></details>
      <details> <font color ="#4CC7D3"><b>frontal brake system that controls the front wheel
</b></font><summary>Front Brakes</summary></details>
