      <h2>Wheels</h2>
       <p>Driving peripherals for the bicycle. Contains the components that contribute to the speed and control.</p>
      <details class="animation"><summary>Spokes</summary><p><font color ="#4CC7D3"><b>connects wheel rim to hub. Usually wire with one end swaged to form a head and one threaded end</b></font></p></details>
      <details> <font color ="#4CC7D3"><b>the core of a wheel; contains bearings and, in a traditional wheel, has drilled flanges for attachment of spokes</b></font><summary>Hub</summary></details>
      <details> <font color ="#4CC7D3"><b>Inner component that protects the tire rubber</b></font><summary>Rim</summary></details>
